NLi9L19d7EZoa0NCEkYjeK7K6BmLVrxg0kehD2iCKH-XI1li4qhmia2jNsYHQqL\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating scaffold setup**\\n\\nI'm looking into whether the normal scaffold has Scala dependencies. The setup categories seem to refer back to earlier scaffolds and existing tests. I'm noticing a conflict with support for version 3.11.0 versus 3.9.4. It makes me wonder if the generation process is using an existing test setup. There's also a consideration about whether to add an \\\"extra Maven dependency\\\" for the Scala compiler, but we need to ensure we’re aligning with standard practices.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering TLS setup**\\n\\nI’m pondering whether to use `org.bouncycastle:bcpkix-jdk18on` for TLS keystore generation, but it seems unnecessary since Java KeyStore APIs should suffice. I should gather the API dependencies through the POM. I also want to include a concise JSON summary referencing documentation and dependencies without markdown. It might be helpful to outline two potential risks and provide guidance, but the user mentioned to choose \\\"no_action\\\" unless additional setup is needed. So I might keep the guidance empty in that case.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Clarifying agent guidance**\\n\\nThe prompt mentions to include environment variables, system properties, and other test-code setup in the agent guidance. This guidance can be present when there's no deterministic setup. I'm trying to understand if \\\"advisory_preparation\\\" means there's no deterministic action but still requires some guidance. However, it also states that while setup can include environment or system properties, it's not a requirement. So, there isn’t a strict mandate to set these elements.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"no_action\",\n  \"summary\": \"fs2-io_3 3.11.0 is usable with its normal transitive dependencies for meaningful file, resource, local networking, process, and TLS coverage; no external service, Docker image, system property, or library-specific extra dependency is required.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"The artifact declares optional com.github.jnr:jnr-unixsocket for Unix socket fallback, but on JDK 21 fs2 uses the JDK Unix-domain-socket implementation, so do not add jnr-unixsocket unless explicitly testing the fallback path.\",\n    \"Network and TLS tests should remain self-contained with localhost/in-process servers or JDK TLS/key-store APIs; relying on external endpoints would be unnecessary and brittle.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0c1efea4e79d964d016a28d0039afc81949c6d63b23bc7cf45\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 3425, "output": 701, "cacheRead": 27648, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 31774, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1781059570499, "responseId": "resp_0c1efea4e79d964d016a28cff47f688194a119e02b315b45b7"}, "toolResults": []}
